events.name: Actions On Google
events.description:
Build Actions with GDG is an open and modular event series designed by GDG and offered to community organizers worldwide.

Actions on Google is a developer platform that lets you create software to extend the functionality of the Google Assistant, Google's virtual personal assistant, across more than 500 million devices, including smart speakers, phones, cars, TVs, headphones, and more.
We invite the developer community to learn about creating Actions for the Google Assistant. Packed with engaging talks and interactive codelabs, the events will surely be memorable for developers who are eager learn more about the exciting new technologies that are coming up.

Registration Link : https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1GxhK9fnWLWiat5QXzpZDRfyWuRtjMjeWpBdD0nD4Gpw/edit

events.name: DevCommunity Roadshow 2019
events.description:
Details
DevCommunity Roadshow 2019 is an event where the developer gets together to watch and explore the upcoming and existing technology. Roadshow aims to bring together a mix of Google practitioners from industry experts, academic researchers, data scientists and self-taught individuals to help learn, discover and build.

DevCommunity Roadshow 2019 is large, community-run events that can offer speaker sessions across multiple product areas, all-day hack-a-thons, code labs, and more. The hackathon will be focused on three areas, Mobile, Web and Internet of Things(IoT). Come out and join us for a day full of fun and meaningful sessions.

The focus of the workshop is materializing an integrated community of developers making it easy for everyone to reach out and help each other in their future endeavors.

Registration Link: https://gdgjalandhar.page.link/roadshow-2019

Date: 20th Oct 2019
Time: 9 am to 5.30 pm
Venue: Chandigarh University

Mail: [masked]

*Filling the registration form doesn't guarantee your confirmation for the event. We will be sending a final confirmation mail only to shortlisted attendees after reviewing your details.
